      <h2 class="mt-5" id="path">Becoming a mortgage closer</h2>
      <div class="body-text"><p>A mortgage closer brings the loan across the finish line. After underwriting approves a file, the closer prepares the final closing documents, coordinates with title and escrow, ensures figures and disclosures are accurate, and makes sure everything is in order for signing and funding. Becoming a mortgage closer rewards precise, deadline-driven people who can manage many moving parts without errors.</p>
<p>Closing generally doesn't require an originator license. It's a vital operations role learned largely on the job, and an excellent way to understand the final, high-stakes stage of every loan. Like other support roles, it's typically salaried. People who enjoy the business but want uncapped income often use a closing role to learn the process, then move toward licensed origination.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

