    <div class="container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">An Honest Word</span>
      <div class="story-rule"></div>
      <p class="story-lede">This is a great way in. The biggest income, though, is in origination.</p>
      <p>A mortgage closer role is a real, respected part of the mortgage business and a smart way to break in. But I'll be straight with you, because it's what I'd tell a friend: the highest earning ceiling in this industry belongs to the licensed people who originate loans &mdash; loan officers and mortgage brokers. They're paid on commission with no cap, while support and operations roles are typically salaried.</p>
      <p>I came into mortgages in 2008 and got my license (NMLS #1072866). Seven Scotsman Guide Top Producer honors and $500M+ in closed loans later, here's my honest advice: a mortgage closer role is an excellent place to start and learn the business from the inside &mdash; and if the income and independence of origination appeal to you, getting licensed is more achievable than most people think. Many great originators started exactly in a role like this.</p>
